24 SECTION 1.3.(b) In accordance with G.S. 135-48.24(b) and G.S. 135-48.30(a)(7)
25 which require the State Treasurer to implement procedures that are substantially similar to the
26 provisions of G.S. 58-50-61 for the North Carolina State Health Plan for Teachers and State
27 Employees (State Health Plan), the State Treasurer and the Executive Administrator of the State
28 Health Plan shall review all practices of the State Health Plan and all contracts with, and practices
29 of, any third party conducting any utilization review on behalf of the State Health Plan to ensure
30 compliance with Section 2 of this act no later than the start of the next plan year.
31 SECTION 1.3.(c) Effective July 1, 2025, there is appropriated from the General
32 Fund to the Department of State Treasurer the sum of one million dollars ($1,000,000) in
33 recurring funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to be used to implement the
34 coverage required by this section for the State Health Plan.
35 SECTION 1.3.(d) Except as otherwise provided, this section becomes effective
36 October 1, 2025, and subsection (a) of this section applies as of the start of the next plan year
37 following the effective date.
38
39 PART II. MEDICAID COVERAGE OF BIOMARKER TESTING
40 SECTION 2.1. The Department of Health and Human Services, Division of Health
41 Benefits (DHB), shall ensure coverage for biomarker testing under the laboratory services
42 clinical coverage policies 1S-1 through 1S-13 to the same extent those services are required to
43 be covered by a health benefit plan under G.S. 58-3-216. DHB shall ensure its policies and
44 procedures for the prior authorization of any service covered under this section are in compliance
45 with Section 2.2 of this act.
46 SECTION 2.2.(a) For purposes of this section, the term "urgent prior authorization
47 request" is defined as a request for which a time line for decision longer than 72 hours could
48 seriously jeopardize the beneficiary's life, health, or ability to attain, maintain, or regain
49 maximum function, in the opinion of the beneficiary's healthcare provider.
Page 4 DRH40336-MRa-91

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 2.2.(b) If prior authorization is required for any service covered under
2 Section 2.1 of this act, the time line for completion of a review of that prior authorization request
3 shall be as follows:
4 (1) For urgent prior authorization requests, DHB shall ensure that the prior
5 authorization request is either approved or denied and notice is given to the
6 beneficiary and beneficiary's healthcare provider within 24 hours after DHB
7 receives all information needed to complete a review of the request for prior
8 authorization.
9 (2) For non-urgent prior authorization requests, DHB shall ensure that the prior
10 authorization request is either approved or denied and notice is given to the
11 beneficiary and beneficiary's healthcare provider within 72 hours after DHB
12 receives all information needed to complete a review of the request for prior
13 authorization.
14
15 PART III. EFFECTIVE DATE
16 SECTION 3.1. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
17 law.
